{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CR6k5T6M9nNAi9MpYsMFcm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, Postgres is running and the tables exist. Now let me write the integration test.\n\nLet me now create the integration test file. I'll write a comprehensive test that covers the full lifecycle:\n1. POST /create → 200\n2. DB state verification\n3. Mock on-chain join (set up locked match in mock)\n4. Worker poll → settle\n5. DB state verification (settled)\n6. GET /rounds/:pda → verification response\n\nI need to be careful about:\n1. The mock Connection needs to implement methods that the backend uses, with proper return types\n2. Auth signing with the creator's keypair\n3. DB cleanup between tests\n\n\n4. Setting up the entropy and config account mock data\n\nSetting up test fixtures...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":173,"cache_read_input_tokens":94439,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":173},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"571f6196-8768-4189-b912-c43475f582e6","uuid":"b7e7ab8d-fcaf-469d-93ef-9820865abdd6"}
